# Terraform Conventions

Terraform manages Layer 0 only — the bootstrap layer that creates ArgoCD and initial secrets. After `terraform apply`, day-to-day operations use GitOps (push to `main`).

## What Terraform Owns

- ArgoCD Helm release and configuration
- Root Application CR (`argocd-apps`) and Infisical Application CR
- Bootstrap K8s Secrets (Infisical encryption key, auth secret, machine identity)
- ArgoCD root Application and Infisical Application CRs

## Rules

- Never store plaintext secrets in `.tf` files. All sensitive values go in `terraform.tfvars` (gitignored).
- All variables with sensitive values must have `sensitive = true` in their declaration.
- Use `null_resource` + `local-exec` for Application CRs because `kubernetes_manifest` requires the CRD to exist at plan time.
- Use `--server-side` (and `--force-conflicts` for Infisical) when applying Application CRs via kubectl.
- The Infisical Application is in Terraform (not App of Apps) because its Helm values embed sensitive DB/Redis passwords from tfvars.

## Variable Naming

- Prefix Infisical-related variables with `infisical_`
- Prefix ArgoCD-related variables with `argocd_`
- Use `_password`, `_secret`, `_key` suffixes for sensitive values
